  <summary>10/2/2001--Introduced.
Amends the Internal Revenue Code to establish a two year recovery period for depreciation of computers and other technological equipment. Reduces the recovery period from five to two years under the alternative depreciation system for certain property ( tax-exempt use property, etc.). Reduces the useful life for depreciation of computer software from 36 to 24 months.Establishes a seven year useful life for depreciation of certain auction-acquired telecommunications licences.</summary>
